<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 5:46PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Clarke
County through 630 PM CDT...
At 545 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 4 miles west of Fulton, or 5 miles north of Grove
Hill. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Grove Hill, Whatley and Fulton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
